the long-term expected rate of return on funded assets shown below is established for each benefit plan by
developing a forward-looking, long-term return assumption for each asset class, taking into account factors such as the expected real return for the specific asset class and inflation  a single, long-term rate of return is then calculated as the weighted average of the target asset allocation and the long-term return assumption for each asset class.
